    <item>
      <title>Link, God of Thunder</title>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/461008</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">1b18df3d0c0e87391a7d69adf10149aad1a1f542</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jul 2024 07:52:12 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64d02bd7a89e3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64d02bd97c15f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; 1.2.1 Compatibility&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: Someone mentioned that a lot of my mods were not compatible with the latest version of TotK so I went and updated them&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;I like taking commissions! DM me on discord if you want a mod made. legend5v&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Brings a requested BotW mod to TotK, because of this request: https://gamebanana.com/requests/51498&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Become Thor with Link's new fit! The armour makes you lightning proof, and does that Stormy Weather Attack thing of the Charged Armour. The set replaces the Phantom Armour, with the exception of the helmet as I had nothing to replace it with. The defence is boosted to 25.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Now, for Stormbreaker. It replaces the Giant Boomerang (NON-decayed), and has a base damage of 80. It also has a ridiculous amount of health (more than the Hylian Shield), but is not indestructible. You can find the boomerang yourself somewhere, or use the Guardian Amiibo from BotW to spawn it in. The amiibo will also drop a Thunder Gleeok horn, which is needed to activate your lightning powers. By itself, Stormbreaker will only cast lightning if you hit it against metal. It will come back to you if you throw it, though the success rate is not 100%.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I plan to add a version that adds blue lightning instead of yellow, eventually.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Compatible with version 1.1.1, 1.1.2, and 1.2.0. Includes a YAML file for RESTBL merging.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Known issues: if you swing randomly in the hair, the lightning will spawn about 6 feet aboev where it's supposed to.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;My &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;YT&lt;/span&gt; channel, if you're interested: &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCZvI_4b0gRHgVLTviZo9H2w&lt;/span&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/zap_30004.rar" type="application/vnd.rar"/>
      <category>Player</category>
      <category>Sounds</category>
    </item>
