    <item>
      <title>Vanilla+</title>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/514343</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">04b4e132fe338d739044c19bd928db5c1f57a9bf</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 27 Jun 2024 15:32:52 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66579b89d7572.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6648d1a05a150.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6648d1a10d911.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6648d1a3ee82c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66579a8a7b21e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Poe shenanigans &amp; more&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: Standalone Sniping Phrenic Bow&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tweak&lt;/em&gt;: Dusk bow buff&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tweak&lt;/em&gt;: Gloom weapons durability buff&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tweak&lt;/em&gt;: Gloom recovery cd increase&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tweak&lt;/em&gt;: Poe value buff&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Adjustment&lt;/em&gt;: Dark armor cost rebalance&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Addition&lt;/em&gt;: Trade Poe for Zonaite&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tweak&lt;/em&gt;: Zonai fuse atk bonus buff&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Tweak&lt;/em&gt;: Flux Construct drop rate boost&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span class="OrangeColor"&gt;Description:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;This is my take on Tears of the Kingdom where the design philosophy is to create something that is close to a vanilla experience, but with several tweaks and additions to make the gameplay more streamlined and certain items more interesting, and even includes a fix to a bug in the base game, courtesy of dt12345.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You can continue from where you left off on your current adventure, but a fresh playthrough is recommended to experience all the new changes, making this mod quite fitting for a replay of the game or even a first playthrough if you don't mind some inaccurate UI at times.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You can either keep scrolling down to take a look at a detailed rundown of all the changes made, or you can jump straight into it and start exploring things yourself by going to the &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/download/514343#FileInfo"&gt;downloads&lt;/a&gt; page.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Changes:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;Master Sword:&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Damage: 30 -&amp;gt; 45&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Durability 40 -&amp;gt; 80&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sword Beam Damage: 10 -&amp;gt; 15&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sword Beam Range: 20 -&amp;gt; 60&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Gets Light Dragon parts passive&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Item description updated to reflect changes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bug in vanilla game where fuse only adds extra durability just once fixed (MS needs to recharge once to take effect)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Weapons/Shields:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sea-Breeze Boomerang: Atk 16 -&amp;gt; 27, Durability 20 -&amp;gt; 40, +Wind Burst&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sword of the Hero: Atk 17 -&amp;gt; 25, Durability 27 -&amp;gt; 37, +Reuse Bursting Material&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;White Sword of the Sky: Atk 24 -&amp;gt; 30, +15 Atk vs Gloom, +Cast Sword Beam&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Biggoron's Sword: +Demolisher (Shatter Rock x1.5)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Dusk Claymore: Atk 34 -&amp;gt; 60, +15 Atk vs Gloom, +Gloom Toll&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fierce Deity Sword: Durability 35 -&amp;gt; 70, +Desperate Strength (x2 Atk when Low HP), +Wind Razor effect with Sword Beam visuals&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lightscale Trident: Atk 16 -&amp;gt; 21, +Life Heal&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="SelectedElement"&gt;Dusk Bow: +Triple Shot with 6 deg spread, Arrow Gravity -5 -&amp;gt; -1, Range 40m -&amp;gt; 1.2km, Durability 40 -&amp;gt; 75&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Added 5 new items (Bargainer Statues);&lt;br&gt;Stick of Poking: Atk 0, Durability 100, Price 100 poes&lt;br&gt;Zonaite Stick of Eternal Poking: Atk 0, Durability 10 000, Price 10 000 poes, Zonai fuse bonus&lt;br&gt;Waxed Kite Shield: Def 0, Durability 20, Shield Surfing Damage x0.05 (= 400 durability), Shield Surfing Friction 0.01, Price 100 poes&lt;br&gt;Sniping Phrenic Bow: Atk 100, Durability 10, Arrow Gravity -4, Range 280m, Reload time x1.5, Price 100 poes&lt;br&gt;Small/Large Zonaite: Price 6/60 poes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Hylian Shield: Durability 800 -&amp;gt; 8000&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Zonai fuse atk bonus increased by ~50%: +[3, 5, 10] Atk -&amp;gt; +[5, 8, 15] Atk&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Gloom Club/Sword/Spear have their durability increased: 14/15/16 -&amp;gt; 28/33/38&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sages:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Recast times are all halved&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All sages are now initially a little weaker, but becomes much stronger with Vow + Helm:&lt;br&gt;Damage multiplier x[0.67, 1, 1.34] -&amp;gt; x[0.5, 1, 2], Mineru Atk [-13, 0, +13] -&amp;gt; [-20, 0, +40]&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mineru Back Attachment: Balloon gives lift, increased glide mobility with wing, walk on air with hover stone&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mineru flashlight is stronger: Angle 90 deg -&amp;gt; 120 deg, Distance: 25m -&amp;gt; 50m&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mineru Zonai energy drain when moving reduced: 75 -&amp;gt; 50&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mineru Arms: Given the Zonaite weapons passive for increased fuse efficiency with Zonai parts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Durability of weapons fused to Mineru are uncapped from 15, always uses fused weapon's own currently remaining durability (Requires use of&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://github.com/3096/ipswitch/tree/master" target="_blank"&gt;IPSwitch&lt;/a&gt; for it to take effect on modded Switch console, works by default on emulator)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Zonai devices' durability when fused to Mineru increased to match default duration: 1m:06.67s -&amp;gt; 30m&amp;nbsp;(Requires use of&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://github.com/3096/ipswitch/tree/master" target="_blank"&gt;IPSwitch&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;for it to take effect on modded Switch console, works by default on emulator)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Enemy:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Most enemies now has a chance to drop rupees when defeated, scales with rank/difficulty&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Talus, Frox, Flux Construct, Blupees and Yiga enemies have their drop rates boosted&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ganon enemies gain +50% HP and gets x2 damage attributes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lynels get HP &amp;amp; Base Atk equivalent to a lynel one rank higher, e.g White-Maned has Silver Lynel stats. Silver Lynels I've taken some liberties with and put it somewhere between a vanilla Silver and a BOTW Golden in terms of stats&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lynel fireball damage drastically increased: 1 (+6) -&amp;gt; 60 (+6)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Gleeok HP +25% and their attacks gain +20~25% more Atk. King Gleeok damage bonus multiplier slightly increased: x1.4 -&amp;gt; x1.5&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Player:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Gloom recovery (Lightroot/surface) interval reduced: 1s -&amp;gt; 0.5s,&lt;br&gt;However when already on the surface, initial cooldown before healing is increased: 3s -&amp;gt; 6s&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Gloom damage initial grace period increased: 2s -&amp;gt; 3s,&lt;br&gt;However once you start taking gloom damage, rate is increased: every 2s -&amp;gt; every 1s&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;[Walk, Run] rate: +[0%, 20%] -&amp;gt; +[5%, 40%]&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Atk, Def and Speed can now stack to 6 using Armor + Food: Atk +[20%, 30%, 50%, 70%, 80%, 100%], Def +[4, 12, 24, 28, 36, 48], Speed Up +[10%, 20%, 30%, 40%, 50%, 60%]&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Large/Grand Poe value increased: +5/20 -&amp;gt; +20/100&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Armor:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mystic Armor set can be upgraded (Defence reduces damage before Rupee Padding)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All Weather Atk Up armor sets have their respective Lv. 2 Cold/Hot/Flame resistance or Lightning proof added in their set bonuses so they can be freely used in the environments they were meant to be used in (Replaces UI icon, but previous effects are still there)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Charged armor set has its defence rating reduced to match the others and because it gets the strongest new effect: [3, 5, 8, 12, 20] -&amp;gt; [2, 4, 6, 9, 16]&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Any piece of the Phantom or Evil Spirit armor sets activate fully awakened Master Sword (+30 atk, no durability loss)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Both the Phantom and Evil Spirit armor sets get the Majora's Mask disguise effect added to their set bonuses&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All the armors with the Frighten People set bonus have their defence rating adjusted to match what a 2-star (★★)&amp;nbsp;armor would have given a certain base defence: Tingle 2 -&amp;gt; 5, Evil Spirit 4 -&amp;gt; 6, Phantom 8, Dark Link 3 -&amp;gt; 12&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Zant's helmet defence adjusted to match Midna's helmet: 3 -&amp;gt; 7&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Dark Link armor set gets Stal disguise effect and Lv. 1 Master Sword Beam Up added in its set bonus (Replaces UI icon, does &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;NOT&lt;/span&gt; get Bone Weap. Prof.). Poe cost has been rebalanced to match new strength and new large/grand poe value&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Tingle armor set replaces Night Speed Up set bonus in favour of piece-wise Speed Up&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Soldier's armor set gets piece-wise Defence Up&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All of Link's outfits from past Zelda games (Zelda 1, LA, OoT, WW, TP, SS, BOTW) gets Lv. 1 Master Sword Beam Up (x2) added to their set bonuses&amp;nbsp;and Atk Up increased to Lv. 2 (+20% -&amp;gt; +30%)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Wind Waker armor set gets the Island Lobster Shirt hidden effect added to its set bonus&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ancient Hero's Aspect gets Lv. 2 Atk Up, Lv. 2 Zonai Energy Up, Lv. 2 Master Sword Beam Up (x3) and Bypass Sword Beam Max HP Condition (uses default range) added to its set bonus&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All divine helms now counts towards the set bonus for their respective region's outfits (Desert Voe set bonus is not displayed in UI, but is active)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;del&gt;Zora armor pieces and Vah Ruta helm get Froggy armor set's hidden effect&lt;/del&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Does not take effect as it should atm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Weather Atk Up combo finisher AoE radius increased by 1m: [2, 3, 4]m -&amp;gt; [3, 4, 5]m&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Weather Atk Up charged atk AoE radius increased by 2m: [6, 8, 10]m -&amp;gt; [8, 10, 12]m&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Weather Atk Up charged atk AoE damage multipliers increased by 1: x[1, 3, 5] -&amp;gt; x[2, 4, 6]&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Weather Charge Atk Up charge rate increased: x2 -&amp;gt; x3&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Climb Speed Up: +[0%, 20%, 30%, 50%] -&amp;gt; +[10%, 30%, 60%, 100%]&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Horizontal Climb: +70% -&amp;gt; +200%&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Climb Jump stamina rate: -50% -&amp;gt; -70%&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Swim Speed Up: +[0%, 30%, 60%, 100%]&amp;nbsp;-&amp;gt; +[10%, 50%, 100%, 200%]&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Swim Dash stamina rate: -70% -&amp;gt; -80%&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Glide Speed Up: +[0%, 50%, 100%, 150%]&amp;nbsp;-&amp;gt; +[10%, 50%, 100%, 200%]&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Charged Atk stamina rate: -50% -&amp;gt; -70%&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Master Sword Beam Up: x1.5 -&amp;gt; x[2, 3]&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Bone Weapon Proficiency: +80% -&amp;gt; +100%&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Gloom Resistance: 1 heart per piece -&amp;gt; 2 hearts per piece (Extra hearts not shown in UI)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Rupee Padding damage limits: [3, 6, 9] hearts -&amp;gt; [4, 8, 12] hearts&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Light footprint interval reduced: 5s -&amp;gt; 4s&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Light footprint area of effect increased: 5m -&amp;gt; 10m&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Light footprint duration increased: 30s -&amp;gt; 3m&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Glow effect AoE increased: [3, 6, 12]m -&amp;gt; [5, 10, 20]m&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Slip Resistance effectiveness +50%: Slip every [2, 6, 8, 10]s -&amp;gt; Slip every [3, 9, 12, 15]s&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Evaporation Down rate: -[20%, 30%, 50%] -&amp;gt; -[20%, 40%, 70%]&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Zonai Energy Up drain rate: -[20%, 35%, 50%] -&amp;gt; -[20%, 40%, 70%]&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Zonai Energy Recharge Up recovery rate: +50% -&amp;gt; +100%&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;Zonai devices:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Wing and Balloon duration increased to default: 1m:15s/2m -&amp;gt; 30m&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Rocket duration increased but energy drain is doubled (matches avarage cannon drain): Duration 3s -&amp;gt; 30s (Rocket jumps from shield/Mineru still have an internal kill switch after a certain gained height), Energy Drain 0.15 wells/s -&amp;gt; 0.3 wells/s&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Beam Emitter damage is doubled, but energy drain is increased by 50%: Atk 12 -&amp;gt; 24, Energy Drain 0.18 wells/s -&amp;gt; 0.27 wells/s&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Time Bombs and Cannons' damage adjusted to match Bomb Flower: 30/12 -&amp;gt; 40&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lights are stronger: Angle 75 deg -&amp;gt; 90 deg, Distance 50m -&amp;gt; 100m&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;Desired changes not yet implemented:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mystic Armor set has a set bonus that increases rupee drops from enemies on defeat or on hit (Blupee effect)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Known issues:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;If you plan to upgrade the Mystic Armor on a save file that already has completed the final trade with Koltin, you need to use a &lt;a href="https://www.marcrobledo.com/savegame-editors/zelda-totk/" target="_blank"&gt;save editor&lt;/a&gt; to gen 63 Bubbul gems (After using the mod is fine, Koltin only takes 38 gems in final trade)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Technical details:&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Game compatibility: v. &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;1.1.1&lt;/span&gt;, v. &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;1.1.2&lt;/span&gt;, v. &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;1.2.0&lt;/span&gt;, v. &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;1.2.1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mod compatibility: If you're using another mod that modifies the same Mals files, RSDB files or System/Resource/ResourceSizeTable file, you can try to use these respective tools to merge them: &lt;a href="https://github.com/ArchLeaders/MalsMerger" target="_blank"&gt;Mals Merger&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://github.com/MasterBubbles/rsdb-merge" target="_blank"&gt;RSDB Merge&lt;/a&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/tools/15857"&gt;RESTBL Calculator&lt;/a&gt;. For any other file that clashes, you must pick which one to remove or try to manually merge changes yourself with something like&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/tools/16655"&gt;Totkbits&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;for Pack/Actor files, or hold out until &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/wips/81203"&gt;TKMM&lt;/a&gt; releases&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Language compatibility: New and modified item descriptions is only supported for EU &amp;amp; US English, other languages will get MsgNotFound for new items and old descriptions for modified items.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Install instructions can be found on the &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/download/514343#FileInfo"&gt;file info&lt;/a&gt; page&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Please report any &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/issues/514343"&gt;issues&lt;/a&gt; you encounter&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Tools mainly used:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/tools/16655"&gt;Totkbits&lt;/a&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://github.com/zeldamods/event-editor" target="_blank"&gt;Event-Editor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://github.com/NX-Editor/NxEditor" target="_blank"&gt;NX-Editor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://github.com/NationalSecurityAgency/ghidra" target="_blank"&gt;Ghidra&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;+ &lt;a href="https://github.com/Adubbz/Ghidra-Switch-Loader" target="_blank"&gt;SwitchLoader&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;plugin&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;I'm still relatively new to modding, especially when it comes to reverse engineering, so if any skilled modders have any tips, information or other that could teach me how to implement the changes outlined in the &lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;Desired changes&lt;/span&gt; section, that would be greatly appreciated and I'll give you a special thanks in the credits&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
